\pard\f0\fs28 Annuals to perennials. Leaves entire, toothed or pinnatifid. Petals usually with dilated base (claw) and lobed distal portion (limb); bases of stamens forming a disc which is often produced dorsally; carpels and stigmas 3 or 4; ovary unilocular; capsule opening more widely at maturity.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Leaf-shape is very plastic in most species. It is necessary to observe carefully the shape and dissection of the petals when using the key and care should be taken to distinguish between the upper and the lateral petals.
\par

